0 -1.20068 TD
(Eye:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( Produces irritation, characterized by a burning sensation, redness, tea\ring, )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(inflammation, and possible corneal injury. May cause transient corneal i\njury. In the eyes )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(of a rabbit, 0.1 ml of 70% isopropyl alcohol caused conjunctivitis, irit\is, and corneal )Tj
T*
(opacity. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
T*
(Skin:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( May cause irritation with pain and stinging, especially if the skin is \abraded. )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(Isopropanol has a low potential to cause allergic skin reactions; howeve\r, rare cases of )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(allergic contact dermatitis have been reported. May be absorbed through \intact skin. )Tj
T*
(Dermal absorption has been considered toxicologically insignificant. The\ cases of deep )Tj
T*
(coma associated with skin contact are thought to be a consequence of gro\ss isopropanol )Tj
T*
(vapor inhalation in rooms with inadequate ventilation, rather than being\ attributable to )Tj
T*
(percutaneous absorption of isopropanol per se. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
T*
(Ingestion:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( Causes gastrointestinal irritation with nausea, vomiting and diarrhea. \May )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(cause kidney damage. May cause central nervous system depression, charac\terized by )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(excitement, followed by headache, dizziness, drowsiness, and nausea. Adv\anced stages )Tj
T*
(may cause collapse, unconsciousness, coma and possible death due to resp\iratory failure. )Tj
T*
(Aspiration of material into the lungs may cause chemical pneumonitis, wh\ich may be )Tj
T*
(fatal. The probable oral lethal dose in humans is 240 ml \(2696 mg/kg\),\ but ingestion of )Tj
T*
(only 20 ml \(224 mg/kg\) has caused poisoning. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
T*
(Inhalation:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( Inhalation of high concentrations may cause central nervous system effe\cts )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(characterized by nausea, headache, dizziness, unconsciousness and coma. \May cause )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(narcotic effects in high concentration. Causes upper respiratory tract i\rritation. Inhalation )Tj
T*
(of vapors may cause drowsiness and dizziness. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
T*
(Chronic:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( Prolonged or repeated skin contact may cause defatting and dermatitis. \)Tj
