(Skin:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( In case of contact, flush skin with plenty of water. Remove contaminate\d clothing )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(and shoes. Get medical aid if irritation develops and persists. Wash clo\thing before reuse. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
0 -1.2 TD
(Ingestion:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( Potential for aspiration if swallowed. Get medical aid immediately. Do \not )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(induce vomiting unless directed to do so by medical personnel. Never giv\e anything by )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(mouth to an unconscious person. If vomiting occurs naturally, have victi\m lean forward. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
T*
(Inhalation:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( If inhaled, remove to fresh air. If not breathing, give artificial resp\iration. If )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(breathing is difficult, give oxygen. Get medical aid. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
0 -1.2 TD
(Notes to Physician:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( Urine acetone test may be helpful in diagnosis. Hemodialysis )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(should be considered in severe intoxication. Treat symptomatically and s\upportively. )Tj
17.5 0 0 17.5 155.5175 567.13887 Tm
(Section 5 - Fire Fighting Measures )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
12.92308 0 0 12.92308 10 516.04239 Tm
(General Information:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( As in any fire, wear a self-contained breathing apparatus in )Tj
T*
(pressure-demand, MSHA/NIOSH \(approved or equivalent\), and full protect\ive gear. )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(Vapors may form an explosive mixture with air. Use water spray to keep f\ire-exposed )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(containers cool. Flammable liquid and vapor. May form explosive peroxide\s. Vapors are )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(heavier than air and may travel to a source of ignition and flash back. \Vapors can spread )Tj
T*
(along the ground and collect in low or confined areas. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
T*
(Extinguishing Media:)Tj
/TT0 1 Tf
( Water may be ineffective. Do NOT use straight streams of water. )Tj
0 -1.20068 TD
(For large fires, use dry chemical, carbon dioxide, alcohol-resistant foa\m, or water spray. )Tj
0 -1.2 TD
(For small fires, use carbon dioxide, dry chemical, dry sand, or alcohol-\resistant foam. )Tj
T*
(Cool containers with flooding quantities of water until well after fire \is out. )Tj
/TT1 1 Tf
